#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enter a word or series of words in the search box, the application "
"will filter the table to only display lines having these words (logical "
"operator AND)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to add (logical operator OR) some lines, you must prefix your "
"word with \"+\"."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:592
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to remove (logical operator NOT) some lines, you must prefix "
"your word with \"-\"."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to search only one column, you must prefix your word with the "
"column name, like: col1:word."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to use the character \":\" in value, you must specify the column "
"name, like: col1:value:rest."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to search for a phrase or something that contains spaces, you "
"must put it in quotes, like: \"yes, this is a phrase\"."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can also use operator \"&lt;\" and \"&gt;\"."
msgstr "También puede usar los operadores «&lt;» y «&gt;»."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below are some examples that can illustrate these rules in a more intuitive "
"way:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid "+val1 +val2 =&gt; Keep lines containing val1 OR val2"
msgstr "+val1 +val2 =&gt; conservar las líneas que contengan val1 o val2"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid "+val1 -val2 =&gt; Keep lines containing val1 but NOT val2"
msgstr "+val1 -val2 =&gt; conservar las líneas que contengan val1 pero no val2"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:604
#, no-c-format
msgid "\"abc def\" =&gt; Keep lines containing the sentence \"abc def\""
msgstr ""
"\"abc def\" =&gt; conservar las líneas que contengan la expresión «abc def»"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:605
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "\"-att:abc def\" =&gt; Remove lines having a column name starting by abc "
#| "and containing \"abc def\""
msgid ""
"\"-att:abc def\" =&gt; Remove lines having a column name starting by att and "
"containing \"abc def\""
msgstr ""
"\"-att:abc def\" =&gt; eliminar las líneas que tengan una columna cuyo "
"nombre empiece por «abc» y contenga «abc def»"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"abc:def =&gt; Keep lines having a column name starting by abc and containing "
"def"
msgstr ""
"abc:def =&gt; Conservar las líneas que tengan una columna cuyo nombre "
"empiece por «abc» y contenga «def»"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ":abc:def =&gt; Keep lines containing \"abc:def\""
msgstr ":abc:def =&gt; conservar las líneas que contengan «abc:def»"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Date&gt;2015-03-01 =&gt; Keep lines where Date attribute is greater than "
"2015-03-01"
msgstr ""
"Fecha&gt;2015-03-01 =&gt; conservar las líneas cuyo atributo «Fecha» sea "
"mayor que 2015-03-01"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amount&lt;10 =&gt;Keep lines where Amount attribute is less than 10"
msgstr ""
"Importe&lt;10 =&gt; conservar las líneas cuyo atributo «Importe» sea menor "
"que 10"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:616
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save Customized Content"
